The top of a lantern is shaped like a square pyramid. The side lengths of the base are equal. Find the surface area of the top of the lantern.

\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.8]
% Draw the square pyramid
\draw[thick] (0,0) -- (2,0) -- (2.5,1) -- (0.5,1) -- cycle;
\draw[thick] (1.25,3) -- (0,0);
\draw[thick] (1.25,3) -- (2,0);
\draw[thick] (1.25,3) -- (2.5,1);
\draw[thick, dashed] (1.25,3) -- (0.5,1);
\draw[thick] (2,0) -- (2.5,1);
\draw[thick] (0.5,1) -- (2.5,1);
% Labels
\node[right] at (2.6,2) {5 in.};
\node[left] at (0.2,1.8) {6 in.};
% Cylinder below pyramid (lantern body)
\draw[thick] (0.3,-0.5) arc (180:360:0.95 and 0.3);
\draw[thick, dashed] (0.3,-0.5) arc (180:0:0.95 and 0.3);
\draw[thick] (0.3,-0.5) -- (0.3,-2.5);
\draw[thick] (2.2,-0.5) -- (2.2,-2.5);
\draw[thick] (0.3,-2.5) arc (180:360:0.95 and 0.3);
\end{tikzpicture}
